<blockquote>
<p>He tried to touch me.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>He said it was to take fluid samples from my–</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Uh&#8230; in real life, when one needs to perform medical procedures on women, it is usually a female who does it (for obvious reasons). I'm sure they could get a female employee to retrieve fluid samples from a female anomalous humanoid.</p>
<p>In any case, the plot point about a researcher behaving inappropriate at work to a test subject is jarring and not-all-that-logical.</p>

