														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2321444">
									

<p>I don't think it worked out for me, due to the point I've addressed above. Regardless of the nature of the test, if it were medically related, it's more likely to be conducted by a female if the subject's a female.</p>
<p>To me, it shows a level of incompetency in the Foundation rather than opening up the window of humanisation.</p>
<p>Instead, you can focus directly on how they (as in, all 4 of them) feel about being a plaything for the Foundation and flesh out each of the 4 as individual characters. I've realised it's rather focused on -C, but what about the others?</p>

							</div>

								
